	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jun 28th 3:44 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=124705><span id=Scholar>Deckert</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>31 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.75]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p><br>Wanted to make some comments on the warrior twilight quests in general, then some specific ones about this weap.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Verant obviously put a lot of time into developing and implementing these quests, but i think the rewards should be re-examined a bit.  I like the fact that the drops are all in zones where a level 40/45/even 50 character can get some nice exp groups and have a great time.  The problem ive found is there are too many equal or better armor/weap alternatives available to a level 40-45ish person to make doing these quests attractive. <br><br>I think this is definately the case with this sword.  While hunting in Tenebrous, we stopped in to kill some Grimlings and we got four 12/29 picks that are .4 weight and go in either hand. I also got a 8/18 1hb off the tribals in Dawnshroud while hunting there.  Obviously the sword is better than the pick, but 12/29 for the amount of running around to do this is pretty lame. Point of mentioning these two drops is that you can easily match this weap at level 40-45 without breaking a sweat and travelling all over the moon.   Also, this is just the free drops i happened to get along the way.  If you consider what the average level 45 warrrior can buy, this weapon is even more ridiculous.  Some extremely cheap and common alternatives that are very close or better than Soldier's are Centi SS, Centi Warhammer, Sarnak Skullsplitter, Crys Spider Fang, and probably a bunch i've overlooked.  A strong case could even be made for a Velium Short Blade over Soldier's.  <br><br>Really dissappointing that these quests dont have people swarming all over the moon, getting people grouped and interacting, and enjoying some quality quests for a change. The infrastructure for these quests is already there, but the rewards are not enticing enough to generate a lot of interest. In the case of this sword, I would consider 12/25ish with same stats a more appropriate reward.<br><br>Kinda long winded of me, but needed to vent a little over what i see as a missed opportunity by Verant to keep people excited over doing quests.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Frostpaw<br>65 Barbarian Warrior<br>Cazic Thule Server</td></tr>
